==English==
====Etymology====
Via French from Latin ''haemorrhoidae''; from Greek '''haemo''', 'blood', '''rhein''', 'flow'; akin to [[hemorrhage]].
===Noun===

{{en-noun}}
# (usually plural) An [[engorge]]d, [[dilate]]d and easily broken [[varicosity]] in the [[perianal]] area, often accompanied by intense itching and throbbing pain: [[piles]].

